<p>So, the logical conclusion is that...gay people, being very unlikely to have accidentally children, do not <strong>need</strong> to get married. Well, okay. I'll buy that also, pretending I am unaware of other reasons to get married.</p>
<p>Now, why are people barring them from getting married? We know they don't <em>need</em> to be in the straightjacket that, apparently, marriage is (1)...but why can't they get in if they <em>want</em> to?</p>
